reviews.text: A really nice and informative museum about the struggles this country had, with a brief history since the Portuguese colonization through very detailed information of the Indonesian occupation and the Timorese uprisings against it. It is a very small museum, so you wouldn’t need more than two hours there. 1$ entry fee. Definitely worth it, it’s good to know the history of this special nation.

A must go if you are visiting the country, although all information contained in this museum can be found on the internet. They do tend to omit a few important and historic facts (e.g. FRETILIN importance to the struggle for independence).

excellent place to know the history how Timorense struggle for their Independence since Portuguese colonization and Indonesian occupation. 
This small museum will makes you discover all unique and tragic history of Timor-Leste event you only spend one day in Dili, because it only takes one hours with 1 dollar entry fee.
A pretty good museum in Dili. Show the Timor Leste people how to struggle for there independence.
A small museum outlining a brief history of Timor leste. It is very informative and a little confronting. I think it is important when visiting a country to try to learn a bit of their history.

Good range of books and an ambience to indulge in thumbing the eye catching titles, with a good spread of gadgetry and toys. Surprising to see decline in the range offered in diaries and calendars while a rise in generic stationary items. Highly trending in non fiction titles is another aspect of 2019 at landmark books arena.. Very encouraging changes in layout of stores, so that one feels like spending time there.

One of the best places to go to if you're a person who just loves spending your time amongst books. They have the perfect collection of books.. books of all categories.. also a comic book haven for comic book fans. They have a dedicated section when people can read books too. 
Apart from books, they have a wide collection of toys for children as well as action figures for collectibles and enthusiasts. 
Fashion accessories, unique forms of diaries, office supplies, bags, mugs, and chocolates are some of the other things that can be found here.

I had been to Landmark which is in Forum, it has developed over a timeframe as far as inside and quality also. Milestone is one stop arrangement on the off chance that you are a book significant other. You have all the assortment of books running from anecdotal, magazines, recorded, instructive and so forth. They have great assortment of books for children too, I like the flawless story books for them.

The games activity is likewise great and contains all the fundamental necessities for all the game. We had purchased a cycle from that point, the conveyance for which was entirely quick. A dazzling spot for book significant others.

Nice place to find books..... And you also get cute stuffs... Not to mention the toy section.... Oh boy!!! .... Doesn't matter how old I get, I will always go in there to check out those cute stuffed toys and marvel avenger figures!!

The shop is good. The collection of books and games is good ( online price is much cheaper). But the staff is untrained. They asked me debit card pin stating ATM machine under charging instead of asking cash as alternative. They did not serviced me to another queue for payment. The payment processing takes more than 30 minutes in queue. Very slow staff.
Nice place for lunch
Delicious javanese food in town!. I tried nasi babat gongso and sate kambing & ayam, and want to try ayam goreng kampung next visit

Indonesian restaurant located in Bidau, Dili. Delicious, reasonable price. You could choose dishes and rice for the quick served meal, or order some food that need to be prepared.
Typically crowded during lunch time. Most of the time the food were running out if we came at 2pm. Recommended, especially for Indonesian.
Many food choices. Little bit pricey
one of the best place to go for Indonesian food.....nice and friendly staff/owner...usually crowded during lunch time...

Love this place. It's great for when I need to feed the whole family or the hubby and I just want to sneak off for a fabulous tasting meal. The coffee is Amazing! The service is impeccable. Definitely a hidden treasure.

This place is great! The food was delicious, everyone working was kind, i enjoyed the atmosphere its like a cozy dinner. They had some homemade baklava too it was Amazing! Love the breakfeast food :) will be stopping by again.
This is an excellent place to eat. A very family friendly and welcoming place. With great food and service.

Such good food, amazing prices, and amazing employees/owners. So welcoming and kind. Great service and it feels so small town like everyone knows you. Will surely keep visiting even after moving out of the area. Love that they offer to go orders!!
Poor customer service, over priced for basic items and very inconsiderate. I feel like I'm eating a more expensive McDonalds only it's worse.

Good service and nice sea view. Smell from the street spoils the view a little bit. Rich choice of hamburgers and pizzas. Pizzas a bit too hard. Some more yeast would probably be helpful. Prices a bit too high. Nice atmosphere and quick service. Mastercard same as in other places - not accepted.
If your in Dili this is a great spot for food and drinks
Drinks half price from 5 to 7, includes cocktails so that's $2.50. Great meals and good service.

The bar and restaurant located at the 1st level of a wooden house. Getting right up the stair you will see a mini bar. The foods range from $9 to $20, consider a bit expensive in Dili. Less than a mile from Centro supermarke, can easily identify when driving along street pantai kelapa. No parking space here, most guests are to park at road side. The ambient is quite nice, live band performance available on selective days. Make Reservation before you visit, it can be crowded especially during dinner time.
My burger tasted not that good, no tomatoes no cucumber, only one piece of crispy chicken, lettuce and soggy bread. What worse is staffs are super cunning and not polite.
Service apartment and can use for one day

The hotel staffs are friendly and they try their best to make your stay as comfortable as possible.
Room is big and spacious, clean. Sleep is good. Mosquitoes can be a handful. Internet speed is stable, though basic as with the rest of this country.

Clean room and guarded compound. Walking distance to the beach. Quite surprise a good hotel amist not so good city. 

A big hug to the friendly staff Rita and Jenny for their hospitality throughout my 2 weeks stay here.
never bean there soz
Ya

I was told the fish burger was out of stock after ordering and waiting for it for almost an hour. There were only 2 groups of people at that moment, so I was wondering what took them so long to tell me. So disappointing.

Perhaps my favorite place to get a sandwich in town. I recommend the chicken avocado mozzarella sandwich or the chicken Tandoori sandwich with yogurt on the side. I really like their shoestring fries but I wish that the portion size was a little bit more because it's frankly just a bit skimpy. The atmosphere is trendy never too crowded. They do have high chairs for young children though I've never seen kids there. When you order tea they give you a whole pot not just a cup. The accepted credit card but might charge you a fee.
The food is pretty good and you'll find (western) variety.  The great thing is the ambiance though.
Tried the pizza, it was very good. Coffee is very good too, maybe the best coffee you can find in Timor Plaza. Expensive.
Love the coffee and layout of the space

I go into Burger King on Wednesday because I meet up with a friend. We are at least in Burger King 3 times a month we usually have ice tea. But once in awhile will have something to eat. It's always clean and so are the bathrooms. Which I have to say I love the up-to-date look in Burger King. I especially like the way they designed the bathrooms. I like knowing I have privacy when I go into the bathroom.  Its become our favorite spot to catch up.
I really love their whoppers and their fries. I ordered a 10 piece chicken nuggets for a reasonable price. Always love Burger King anywhere I go and definitely recommend this place.
Usually really fast service, except during lunch hour. Great customer service as well
Had a bacon csburger, the hamburger was the size of a 50ct. Coin with 1 slice of bacon, the top of the bun was bigger than the meal.. very small hamburger, never again. Half star for the French fries
Very Clean and great service.  Awesome people. I felt welcomed.
Really tasty and fresh Indonesian food at affordable prices. Wide range of vegetarian options!
Very wide range of Indonesian food: capcay, tempeh curry, beef, fish, etc. Big portions and affordable prices.
good food, $4.50 for this plate
Spicy restaurant

This is the best Chinese resto I know in Timor Leste. The best thing is about the service, very nice and friendly.

The place is very clean and comfortable. The price is affordable and the food is delicious. 

I very appreciate this restaurant.

One of my favourite places to eat lunch or dinner. Although menu are the same almost 10 years now, loyal customer always keep coming because taste are different to other reataurant. Lemon chicken, cream of chicken soup are some of my fav foods.

It was fascinating to discover south east asia foods in Dili. The owner was originally from Malaysia. The menu offer variety of popular foods from south east asia. Hokkien noodle, Loh Mee, curry mee, wan tan mee. These name may sound peculiar to you but a typical Malaysian will know these are some favourite foods from south east asia. Price are moderate, if you miss local foods!! Try it out.
Good food..but lil bit expensive
great food
One of the better sea front restaurants. Large portion size and the beef dishes are excellent. Haven’t tried the fish dishes yet.

The best Chinese restaurant in Dili! Quality of the food is very good and delicious. The quantity is big as well. Big portion! 
Sweet and sour pork rice, curry pork rice, seafood pot tofu, Hong Kong fried noodles, Chinese fried kueh tiaw, Hong Kong seafood crispy noodles... all very nice! For Wanton noodles - still have room for improvement! Thumbs up after all!
Always excellent food and service
Great Chinese food with fresh Tiger Beer on tap!
Chinese inspiration for that beachside restaurant where my plate was bland and the staff uote distracted. Should have gone somewhere else along the beach!
Delicious pizza i ever taste
Good quality of fuel & open 24/7 (the only one in town).
One of the best spot for Pizza
Nice 24 hours open. Shop and fuel station

Great Portuguese food in Timor. Portions are generous and service is good. The owner of the restaurant is generally around to ensure quality and greet customers. Prices will be around $30 or so person if drinking.
Nice Place👌
Very good service! Great place for post-event dinner.
Great quality food.. The service is not always the best though
Porto chef... Nice place to eat and talk... Good food... Recommend baramundi...

Good food and well prepared Suchi, maybe best in Dili.
Be aware only cash no credit cards.

I love Japanese food.  Not brave enough to try sushi here yet though. I ordered the cold ramen. You know that cucumber dish often served in Thai restaurants (in the States),  the cucumber in the dish tastes just like that (minus the chilis). If you don't like vinegar this dish isn't for you. 
I also love iced tea which I've found hard to get in Timor. Until now. The cold jasmine tea without sugar is great.
It used to be better

One of the best Japanese restaurants in dili. They have daily Bento boxes for lunch which are about 10 bucks. They have a very large menu with all types of things from Sushi, tempura, curry and much much more. The place is romantic enough for a date. It has a little cherry blossom tree and a lot of other Japanese decorations. I really like the salmon and tuna sushi rolls. They have good miso soup as well. To get a fifth star they should do three things, 1 never ever run out of green tea - this is a Japanese restaurants after all, 2 make bigger portion sizes for the edamame beans, and 3 get the mosquitoes under control. This place does not accept a credit card.

Well it isn't Mexico, but considering we're in Timor this is pretty good. The small simple restaurant has a two-page menu. Everything from tacos nachos burritos excetera. My favorite is the chicken burrito for $8. For that price you can fill your belly. No credit cards accepted here.

Excellent quality Mexican food,  with most meals coming with very good fresh and cooked veg. Choice of pork/beef/chicken/grilled vegetables. Does take away and delivery.  Oh, and a very functional looking bar there too.
Delicious salsas, guacamole, enchiladas - better than most US Mexican restaurants - $8 per entree is definitely worth it
Very nice Mexico food.
Solid burrito.
We ordered pizza and a side of chips and calamari. Service was fantastic and friendly staff.
One of the best restaurants in Dili. Great pasta and atmosphere. Chief Robison is one of the best in this  town.

Located right in front of Pantai Kelapa, this place serves italian food. Service is superb, staff are friendly, and they accomodated our request for a quick meal - we only had 20 minutes to eat cause we had a movie to catch. They gave us free soup, which was very tasty. Food is delicious and quite pricey. The place is neat and clean, but a bit dark. Perhaps it would look better in the daylight. Good place for couples, friends, and families.
Impeccable service and great food! Could not ask for more!
Basically pizza in a comfortable setting but good enough, really. Good service and fair price. Ok for a quiet night out.
It's really awesome.
Best place to see Aswan
Beautiful View of Aswan City and Mesmerizing Sunset
Marvellous view
Fantastic
